                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "PURPOSE"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 9,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The purpose of this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is to:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 10,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Document and standardise the process for recording referral from dentists and opticians manually in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "** Please note that all GP referrals into MEHT must be via the eRS."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Document and standardise the process for tracking and updating the patient's pathway status to ensure accurate RTT information is recorded"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 13,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Provide a baseline for future process improvements"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Assist in developing baseline for the development of training material"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Please refer to the OPD01 \u2013 Outpatients: Referral Management and Access Planning for a detailed description of end to end outpatient procedure."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 16,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Overview"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Referrals received directly from primary care providers e.g. dentists and opticians should be recorded manually into Lorenzo. The 18 week RTT pathway of these referrals will start in Lorenzo when the referral has been triaged and managed as accepted in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Additional guidance"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Prior to adding a new referral to a patient's record, the user must review the active referrals in the referrals tab of patients EPR in Lorenzo, to see if the patient has an active referral in the same service. If this is the case then a new referral must not be created as this will start a new pathway in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Staff must escalate referrals that have incomplete details to their supervisor before this can be added to Lorenzo EPR."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Role: Administrative \u2013 Booking clerk"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Procedure: Recording a referral from the dentist / optometrist or optician in Lorenzo"
